1
00:00:05,191 --> 00:00:08,380
The great writers 
seduce us,

2
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:15,870
through story, into dealing 
with the “big questions”.

3
00:00:15,990 --> 00:00:20,030
[The Great Themes in Literature]

4
00:00:20,131 --> 00:00:23,733
That’s mentioned 
in that Chekhov story,

5
00:00:23,913 --> 00:00:28,713
where a man in Petersburg
is interested in a girl.

6
00:00:28,713 --> 00:00:34,555
She’s much younger than him,
and she’s a musician or singer.

7
00:00:34,555 --> 00:00:36,371
And they made 
sort of a party,

8
00:00:36,371 --> 00:00:39,371
and expressed 
some interest, whatever,

9
00:00:39,371 --> 00:00:43,104
and she gives him a note,
and he reads the note, and it says,

10
00:00:43,104 --> 00:00:47,320
“Meet me in the graveyard 
at midnight.”

11
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,150
[Laughing]

12
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:51,236
And he’s thinking,

13
00:00:51,606 --> 00:00:58,301
“Oh, she’s just playing with me.
This isn’t serious.”

14
00:00:58,301 --> 00:01:00,622
And he is sad, goes home,
and he’s saying,

15
00:01:00,622 --> 00:01:04,290
“I’m not such a fool 
to fall for this kind of thing,

16
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:06,891
I’m not that kind of man …”

17
00:01:06,891 --> 00:01:09,192
That was at around 10:30.

18
00:01:09,552 --> 00:01:11,362
[Laughing]

19
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:13,814
By around 11:15 he thinks,

20
00:01:13,814 --> 00:01:17,161
“What if she actually goes?”

21
00:01:18,681 --> 00:01:24,310
Then he calls his driver
get the horse and a carriage ready,

22
00:01:24,310 --> 00:01:26,371
and the whole thing.

23
00:01:26,461 --> 00:01:30,531
By around 5 minutes 
to midnight he’s there,

24
00:01:30,531 --> 00:01:32,271
in the graveyard.

25
00:01:33,651 --> 00:01:35,781
But she’s not there.

26
00:01:36,081 --> 00:01:38,681
But this is a Chekhov story.

27
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:42,887
So, through that story
where nothing happens,

28
00:01:42,921 --> 00:01:47,437
he brought you to the position
he needs you to be in.

29
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:50,436
So while he’s there
waiting,

30
00:01:50,436 --> 00:01:52,290
he starts going
for a stroll,

31
00:01:52,290 --> 00:01:55,701
and looking 
at all the tombstones,

32
00:01:55,701 --> 00:01:59,031
and he’s seeing,
‘Born this time,

33
00:01:59,031 --> 00:02:01,388
died this time.’

34
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:04,405
And he’s seeing,
‘Men and women.’

35
00:02:04,405 --> 00:02:06,758
And, particularly because 
he was there looking for the woman,

36
00:02:06,758 --> 00:02:09,157
he’s seeing the women
gravestones, and he’s thinking,

37
00:02:09,157 --> 00:02:12,233
“Yes, they were 
beautiful young girls,

38
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:15,940
and they had aspirations, 
and hopes, and lives,

39
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:20,230
and loves, and …
here it ends.”

40
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:23,872
Guru Mahārāj liked 
to quote that Gray’s elegy:

41
00:02:23,904 --> 00:02:26,856
“The boast of heraldry,
the pomp of pow’r,

42
00:02:26,859 --> 00:02:30,219
And all that beauty,
all that wealth e’er gave,

43
00:02:30,219 --> 00:02:32,875
Awaits alike 
the inevitable hour.

44
00:02:32,875 --> 00:02:37,275
The paths of glory
lead but to the grave.”

45
00:02:37,597 --> 00:02:41,830
I was on Ukrainian
television show in Kiev,

46
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:45,560
kind of like “Good morning, Kiev!”
or something,

47
00:02:45,842 --> 00:02:49,207
and there were 
two… male … a man and a woman

48
00:02:49,207 --> 00:02:53,880
doing the interviewing, and 
the woman asked me about

49
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,600
memento mori,

50
00:02:58,770 --> 00:03:01,141
which means—
she was paying attention in school,

51
00:03:01,141 --> 00:03:04,128
when they taught to say—
“What does it mean?”;

52
00:03:05,171 --> 00:03:08,489
The reminder, 
death reminders.

53
00:03:08,489 --> 00:03:10,716
So, the great paintings, 
the great poets,

54
00:03:10,716 --> 00:03:12,956
the great works of art—
that’s one of the issues

55
00:03:12,956 --> 00:03:14,237
that you are going 
to deal with:

56
00:03:14,237 --> 00:03:18,791
love and loss,
and also mortality.

57
00:03:19,391 --> 00:03:25,566
So let’s back
to your question—

58
00:03:25,566 --> 00:03:30,079
to avoid that, 
to not deal with that issue,

59
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:38,271
is to not take advantage
of what human life is about.

